ðŸš€ Project Description

This Python program works as a Tip Calculator.
It asks the user:

Total bill amount

Tip percentage (10, 20, or 30)

Number of people sharing the bill

Then it calculates how much each person should pay.

ðŸ§  Concepts Used

input()

float() and int()

Arithmetic operations

Variables

Basic user interaction

ðŸ’» Code
print("WELCOME TO THE TIP CALCULATOR!")
bill = float(input("What was the total bill?"))
tip = int(input("How much tip would u like to give? 10 20 or 30"))
split = int(input("How many people to split the bill between?"))
bill_to_pay = (bill + tip) / split
print("Each person should pay:")
print(bill_to_pay)
